_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"instagram giveaway\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"rafflepress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=7053\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:384:\"<p>Do you want to run an Instagram giveaway? We\'ll show you how to make a giveaways on Instagram the smart way with this step by step guide.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-make-giveaways-on-instagram/\">How to Make Giveaways on Instagram (the Smart Way)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Stacey Corrin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29309:\"\n<p>Are you looking for easy ways to run an Instagram giveaway? As the most popular social media network for visual content, Instagram&#8217;s the perfect place to create viral giveaways that raise brand awareness and drive traffic to your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;re going to show you how to make giveaways on Instagram the smart way to engage your target audience and skyrocket your business growth.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-table-of-contents uagb-toc__align-left uagb-toc__columns-undefined uagb-block-320e5543\" data-scroll=\"true\" data-offset=\"30\" data-delay=\"800\"><div class=\"uagb-toc__wrap\"><div class=\"uagb-toc__title-wrap\"><div class=\"uagb-toc__title\">Table Of Contents</div></div><div class=\"uagb-toc__list-wrap\"><ul class=\"uagb-toc__list\"><li><a href=\"#1-define-your-reasons-for-running-an-instagram-giveaway\">1. Define Your Reasons for Running an Instagram Giveaway</a></li><li><a href=\"#2-learn-instagrams-rules-for-giveaways\">2. Learn Instagram&#8217;s Rules for Giveaways</a></li><li><a href=\"#3-choose-a-relevant-prize\">3. Choose a Relevant Prize</a></li><li><a href=\"#4-create-your-instagram-giveaway\">4. Create Your Instagram Giveaway</a></li><li><a href=\"#5-promote-your-giveaway-on-instagram\">5. Promote Your Giveaway on Instagram</a></li><li><a href=\"#6-choose-a-giveaway-winner\">6. Choose a Giveaway Winner</a></li><li><a href=\"#7-track-your-giveaway-results\">7. Track Your Giveaway Results</a></li></ul></div></div></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Before we dive in, let&#8217;s look at why creating a giveaway on Instagram is a smart idea for your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Reasons to Make an Instagram Giveaway</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Regardless of whether your brand&#8217;s new to Instagram or you already have an audience, <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/how-to-run-an-instagram-giveaway/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">running an Instagram giveaway</a> or contest is a great way to build relationships with your fans.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Moreover, running a giveaway on Instagram can…</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Help you grow your followers faster than those who don&#8217;t run contests</li><li>Encourage your audience to engage more with your brand, resulting in your content showing more prominently in the feed</li><li>Develop stronger relationships between you and your audience, creating an emotional connection</li><li>Help you tease and preview upcoming products or releases to generate excitement</li><li>Drive followers to create user-generated content you can use as valuable social proof to improve your brand&#8217;s trustworthiness</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Even better, Instagram giveaways can catch the attention of influencers in your niche, which can drive tons of traffic to your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Smart Ways to Make Giveaways on Instagram</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know why creating an Instagram contest is beneficial for your business let&#8217;s get started by showing you how to make a giveaway on Instagram to boost your brand.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Define Your Reasons for Running an Instagram Giveaway</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before you set up your giveaway, you should figure out what you want to get out of running one. This means setting clear goals defining the results you want to achieve. If you don&#8217;t create a set of goals, you&#8217;re not serving your business in a way that helps it grow. Instead, you&#8217;re just giving something away for free without any tangible results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The goals you choose for your contest will impact every decision you make further along in your campaigns like the prize you choose, the type of content you create, and how you&#8217;ll promote your giveaway.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, check out this giveaway from Best in Travel Group.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/maldives-giveaway-example-min.png\" alt=\"Best travel group maldives giveaway example\" class=\"wp-image-7054\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/maldives-giveaway-example-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/maldives-giveaway-example-min-400x255.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The image used for their contest showcases precisely what people have the chance to win and identifies the post as a giveaway.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you look at the caption, you can see their giveaway goal is to grow their Instagram audience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To reach that goal, the conditions for entering include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Commenting on the post</li><li>Tagging a friend</li><li>Following the brand and partner&#8217;s profiles</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>With clear giveaway goals, this brand makes it easier to get the results they want. What&#8217;s more, it also helps participants understand what to expect and how they can enter.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your goals might look different from this example. Here are some ideas that might align more with your business needs and how you can achieve them:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Increase email sign-ups:</strong> ask users to subscribe to enter your giveaway.</li><li><strong>Boost website traffic:</strong> get people to visit a blog post or web page.</li><li><strong>Improve user engagement:</strong> ask users to submit photos featuring your products.</li><li><strong>Raise brand awareness:</strong> get participants to share your giveaway on their social channels.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Learn Instagram&#8217;s Rules for Giveaways</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you know what you want to achieve from your giveaway, it&#8217;s good to check out Instagram&#8217;s rules for running promotions on their platform.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are several <a href=\"https://help.instagram.com/179379842258600\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">guidelines for running contests on Instagram</a> that you&#8217;ll need to follow. Otherwise, you could be at risk of having your giveaway shut down.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To make sure you&#8217;re on the right track, you should include the following information in your giveaway post:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Your rules for entering the giveaway</li><li>Who&#8217;s eligible to enter your contest</li><li>Relevant regulations related to your prize like age restrictions etc</li><li>A statement acknowledging that Instagram isn&#8217;t responsible for the giveaway</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If your rules aren&#8217;t clear, Instagram reserves the right to remove your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you understand these rules and have created a set for your giveaway, you&#8217;re ready to choose a prize.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Choose a Relevant Prize</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>After planning your Instagram giveaway, the next step is to choose a relevant prize. Your prize acts as the bait to reel in participants, so if it isn&#8217;t desirable enough, you won&#8217;t see as much engagement as you&#8217;d like.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Picking a prize is relatively easy if you&#8217;re an eCommerce business or a brand that sells consumer products, as you can offer free products as the prize. However, software companies will need to do a little more research to offer a prize that your audience will love.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/giveaway-prize-ideas-min.png\" alt=\"Instagram giveaway prize ideas\" class=\"wp-image-7055\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/giveaway-prize-ideas-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/giveaway-prize-ideas-min-400x194.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An easy way to do that is to look at your Instagram insights to view an overview of what&#8217;s most relevant to your fans.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Alternatively, you can partner with complementary brands to give away a high-value prize bundle. This is a win-win for everyone involved as each brand can increase product awareness and broaden their audience all at once.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you need more inspiration, check out this list of <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/contest-prize-ideas/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">proven contest prize ideas</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. Create Your Instagram Giveaway</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you&#8217;ve planned your contest, defined your rules, and picked a fantastic prize, it&#8217;s time to start creating your giveaway. The most common approach for this is to create a new post on Instagram and go from there.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yet there are several drawbacks to this approach, such as:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>It&#8217;s challenging to keep track of everyone entering your giveaway</li><li>You can&#8217;t instantly share your giveaway on other social media platforms</li><li>There isn&#8217;t a simple way to collect user-generated content</li><li>There&#8217;s no way to choose a winner automatically</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>For this tutorial, we&#8217;re using <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">RafflePress, the best WordPress giveaway plugin</a>, to make an Instagram giveaway. RafflePress gives you everything you need to build viral contests on Instagram that grow your followers, traffic, and brand awareness.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the drag and drop giveaway builder, you can craft the perfect giveaway in minutes. Pre-built viral giveaway templates make it easy to tailor your contest based on your business goals. And powerful entry options help you broaden your reach beyond your website and Instagram.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What&#8217;s more, you can track everyone who enters right from your WordPress dashboard, and randomly draw a winner when the contest ends. This saves you from having to dig through tons of Instagram posts to figure out who entered.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that in mind, let&#8217;s look at the steps to make giveaways on Instagram using RafflePress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Step 1: Download and Install the RafflePress WordPress Plugin</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Click here to <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">get started with RafflePress</a>, then download the plugin to your computer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then upload the plugin to your WordPress website and activate it. If you need a little help with this, check out this guide to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Step 2: Choose the Instagram Giveaway Template</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Once RafflePress is installed on your website, navigate to <strong>RafflePress » Add New</strong> to create a new giveaway.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This opens a page where you can give your giveaway a name and choose a template. RaffePress&#8217;s pre-built giveaway templates are designed to help you reach your giveaway goals as quickly as possible.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/choose-giveaway-template.png\" alt=\"choose a template for your giveaway\" class=\"wp-image-6808\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/choose-giveaway-template.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/choose-giveaway-template-400x313.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To make a giveaway on Instagram that grows your audience, hover your mouse over the <strong>Grow Your Instagram Following</strong> giveaway template. Then click <strong>Use This Template</strong> to launch the RafflePress giveaway builder.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-template-min.png\" alt=\"Choose the instagram giveaway template\" class=\"wp-image-7058\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-template-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-template-min-400x216.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Step 3: Add Your Prize Details</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Inside the RafflePress giveaway builder, you can start entering your prize details. Clicking the pencil icon next to your giveaway title opens a panel on the right-hand side where you can give your prize a name, description, and upload an image.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/edit-prize-details-min.png\" alt=\"Add your Instagram giveaway prize details\" class=\"wp-image-7059\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/edit-prize-details-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/edit-prize-details-min-400x277.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the left side, you can enter the start and end date for your giveaway and choose your preferred time zone.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/add-instagram-prize-details-min.png\" alt=\"Add the image, time, and start date for your giveaway on Instagram\" class=\"wp-image-7060\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/add-instagram-prize-details-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/add-instagram-prize-details-min-400x303.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you&#8217;re happy with your prize details, click the <strong>Done Editing</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Step 4: Choose Your Entry Options</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>The next step is to choose the ways people can enter your giveaway. With the Instagram giveaway template, the options to visit your profile on Instagram and view an Instagram post or video are added automatically.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click either option to open a panel on the left-hand side where you can enter your Instagram profile or post URL, make the action mandatory, and choose how many entries that action is worth.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-entry-actions-min.png\" alt=\"Entry methods for your Instagram giveaway\" class=\"wp-image-7061\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-entry-actions-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-entry-actions-min-400x335.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To add more bonus entries, click the <strong>Actions </strong>tab, and click any of the actions listed to add it to your giveaway widget.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-actions-min.png\" alt=\"Choose bonus entries for your giveaway\" class=\"wp-image-7062\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-actions-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-actions-min-400x304.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, if you want to encourage viral sharing of your giveaway, click the <strong>plus (+)</strong> icon next to the <strong>Refer-a-Friend &#8211; Viral</strong> action. Then when you click the action in your widget, you can enter instructions for users sharing your giveaway and choose which platforms they can share it on.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/refer-a-friend-actions-min.png\" alt=\"Refer a friend entry method\" class=\"wp-image-7063\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/refer-a-friend-actions-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/refer-a-friend-actions-min-400x335.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Repeat this process for every bonus entry you want to include. Make sure you click <strong>Save</strong> periodically to preserve your settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Step 5: Design Your Instagram Giveaway</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>The next step is to click the <strong>Design</strong> tab to choose the design options for your Instagram giveaway.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the left-hand panel, you can choose from 2 different layouts for your giveaway, change your fonts, and choose a custom button color.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-design-options-min.png\" alt=\"Design your instagram giveaway\" class=\"wp-image-7065\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-design-options-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-design-options-min-400x297.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then in the <strong>Page Background</strong> section, you can choose a color for your <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-a-giveaway-landing-page/\">giveaway landing page&#8217;s</a> background or upload an image from your computer. If you have experience with using CSS, you can enter custom CSS to style your giveaway widget in the box provided.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/giveaway-page-background-min.png\" alt=\"Upload a background image for you giveaway\" class=\"wp-image-7066\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/giveaway-page-background-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/giveaway-page-background-min-400x323.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Step 6: Configure Your Settings</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Now click the <strong>Settings</strong> tab. In the <strong>General Settings</strong> section, you can change your giveaway&#8217;s name, add a custom URL for your <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://rafflepress.com/giveaway-landing-page-examples/\" target=\"_blank\">giveaway landing page</a>, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/giveaway-landing-page-permalink-min.png\" alt=\"General settings to give your giveaway landing page a URL\" class=\"wp-image-7067\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/giveaway-landing-page-permalink-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/giveaway-landing-page-permalink-min-400x227.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>However, one of the most important sections is the <strong>Giveaway Rules</strong>. Clicking this option gives you the ability to enter your giveaway rules directly into the widget for users to see easily.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-rules-min.png\" alt=\"Add rules to your giveaway widget\" class=\"wp-image-7068\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-rules-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-rules-min-400x213.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There&#8217;s also a handy rules generator you can use to create a set of basic contest rules. Simply click the <strong>+Generate Rules</strong> button and answer the questions on the screen, such as your sponsor name, email, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then when you&#8217;re happy, click <strong>Generate Rules</strong> to add your guidelines to your giveaway widget automatically.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/giveaway-rules-generator.png\" alt=\"Instagram giveaway rules generator\" class=\"wp-image-7069\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/giveaway-rules-generator.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/giveaway-rules-generator-400x283.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Step 7: Publish Your Giveaway</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;re almost there…</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now all you need to do is publish your giveaway on your website. RafflePress offers 3 different ways to publish your giveaway, including:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><strong>RafflePress WordPress block:</strong> Use this option to embed your giveaway in a post or page using the WordPress block editor.</li><li><strong>RafflerPress Shortcode:</strong> You can use a shortcode to embed your giveaway in the classic WordPress editor, sidebar widgets, or your WordPress theme.</li><li><strong>Giveaway Landing Page:</strong> This option lets you display your contest on a stunning <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-a-giveaway-landing-page-2/\">giveaway landing page</a> free of distractions.</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to publish your giveaway in a way that maximizes engagement and conversions is to publish your Instagram giveaway using the landing page option.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To do that, click the <strong>Publish</strong> tab at the top of the RafflePress builder and click the <strong>Giveaway Landing Page</strong> option and click <strong>Save</strong> to save your changes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/publish-giveaway-min.png\" alt=\"Publish your instagram giveaway on a landing page\" class=\"wp-image-7070\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/publish-giveaway-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/publish-giveaway-min-400x216.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you click the <strong>View Page</strong> button, you&#8217;ll see a preview of your Instagram giveaway live on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/rafflepress-instagram-giveaway-min.png\" alt=\"Instagram giveaway created with RafflePress\" class=\"wp-image-7071\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/rafflepress-instagram-giveaway-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/rafflepress-instagram-giveaway-min-400x313.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>5. Promote Your Giveaway on Instagram</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve made your Instagram giveaway, you can&#8217;t merely sit back and wait for people to enter. You need to start actively promoting it to ensure as many people participate as possible. Otherwise, you won&#8217;t be able to meet your goals.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step in promoting your giveaway on Instagram is to craft an announcement post to share with your followers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your Instagram giveaway announcement post should include the following information:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>An eye-catching image to get people to stop scrolling and read your caption</li><li>Information about the prize you&#8217;re offering</li><li>Instructions for entering the giveaway</li><li>Your rules and guidelines</li><li>The URL for your giveaway landing page</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Since Instagram doesn&#8217;t let users click links in captions, you can add your giveaway link to your Instagram bio and ask users to click the link in your bio to enter.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-promotion-min.png\" alt=\"Instagram giveaway promotion\" class=\"wp-image-7072\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-promotion-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instagram-giveaway-promotion-min-400x255.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There are also many other ways you can promote your giveaway, including:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Emailing your newsletter subscribers, asking them to join in</li><li>Adding a popup on your website directing visitors to your giveaway landing page</li><li>Adding your contest to <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/28-best-online-sweepstakes-websites-to-promote-your-contest/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">giveaway directory websites</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also check out these <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/contest-promotion-ideas/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">proven contest promotion ideas</a> for more inspiration.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>6. Choose a Giveaway Winner</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When your contest is over, you&#8217;ll need to choose a winner. The easiest and fairest way to <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/how-to-pick-a-winner-of-a-giveaway/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">pick a winner of a giveaway</a> is through a random draw.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s super easy to choose a winner in RafflePress randomly. After the end of your giveaway, navigate to <strong>RafflePress » Giveaways</strong> and click the <strong>Needs Winner</strong> link on your screen&#8217;s right-hand side.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/needs-a-winner.png\" alt=\"choose the needs a winner link\" class=\"wp-image-6820\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/needs-a-winner.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/needs-a-winner-400x250.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This shows a list of everyone who entered the giveaway and how many entries each person has. To randomly select a winner, click the <strong>Pick Winner</strong> button, choose your options, and click <strong>Choose Winners Now</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/choose-a-giveaway-winner.png\" alt=\"Choose a giveaway winner\" class=\"wp-image-7073\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/choose-a-giveaway-winner.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/choose-a-giveaway-winner-400x189.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The winner is then highlighted in the list of participants. Now you can click to email the winner and tell them the great news.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s also good practice to follow up after your giveaway with everyone who entered. You can do that by sending an email newsletter announcing the winner and thanking everyone for joining in.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To keep everyone engaged with your brand and increase the chance of attracting new customers, you can offer a small discount to everyone who entered.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>7. Track Your Giveaway Results</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Your final task is to look at the results of your Instagram giveaway. This helps you learn what you did right and how you can improve future giveaways.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to get the data you need to improve your giveaways is with <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\">MonsterInsights, the best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/monsterinsights-dashboard-get-more-subscribers-800x556.jpg\" alt=\"monsterinsights wordpress dashboard\" class=\"wp-image-5924\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/monsterinsights-dashboard-get-more-subscribers-800x556.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/monsterinsights-dashboard-get-more-subscribers-400x278.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/monsterinsights-dashboard-get-more-subscribers-768x534.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/monsterinsights-dashboard-get-more-subscribers.jpg 1116w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With MonsterInsights, you can easily track visits to your giveaway landing page, general website traffic, referral traffic, and much more. You can also see all your data within your WordPress dashboard, so you won&#8217;t need to leave your site to get the information you need.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the data gathered by MonsterInsights, you can learn which promotion ideas drove the most traffic to your giveaway page. What&#8217;s more, you can use real-time stats to make changes to your contest while it&#8217;s running.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Make Instagram Giveaways to Grow Your Brand</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There you have it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You now know how to make giveaways on Instagram to reward your followers, increase brand awareness, and grow your business. Now all that&#8217;s left is to go and make one yourself.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And with the viral power of RafflePress&#8217;s giveaway builder behind you, you can get started in no time at all and see the results you need.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click here to <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">get started with RafflePress</a> today.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And don&#8217;t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/seedprodwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/seedprod\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Twitter</a> for more helpful tips and tutorials.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-make-giveaways-on-instagram/\">How to Make Giveaways on Instagram (the Smart Way)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"How to Customize a Password Protected Page in WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-password-protected-page-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 15 Jul 2020 14:33:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"How To\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"css hero\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"password protect\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"password protect pages\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"seedprod\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"wpforms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=7005\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:613:\"<p>Are you looking for an easy way to customize password-protected pages on your website? Doing so keeps your branding consistent across your entire site and lets you utilize the space to promote other pages.&#160; But changing the design of locked pages isn’t easy without the help of a developer. That’s why in this article, we’ll [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-password-protected-page-wordpress/\">How to Customize a Password Protected Page in WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Stacey Corrin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25699:\"\n<p>Are you looking for an easy way to customize password-protected pages on your website? Doing so keeps your branding consistent across your entire site and lets you utilize the space to promote other pages.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But changing the design of locked pages isn’t easy without the help of a developer. That’s why in this article, we’ll show you how to customize a password protected page in WordPress without writing a single line of code.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-table-of-contents uagb-toc__align-left uagb-toc__columns-undefined uagb-block-7c812fd5\" data-scroll=\"true\" data-offset=\"30\" data-delay=\"800\"><div class=\"uagb-toc__wrap\"><div class=\"uagb-toc__title-wrap\"><div class=\"uagb-toc__title\">Table Of Contents</div></div><div class=\"uagb-toc__list-wrap\"><ul class=\"uagb-toc__list\"><li><a href=\"#1-customize-password-protected-pages-with-seedprod\">1. Customize Password Protected Pages with SeedProd</a></li><li><a href=\"#2-customize-protected-form-pages-with-wpforms\">2. Customize Protected Form Pages with WPForms</a></li><li><a href=\"#3-customize-protected-form-pages-in-seedprod\">3. Customize Protected Form Pages in SeedProd</a></li><li><a href=\"#4-customize-default-password-pages-with-css-hero\">4. Customize Default Password Pages with CSS Hero</a></li></ul></div></div></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get to it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>When to Customize Password Protected Pages?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are several reasons for wanting to customize locked pages in WordPress. The most common reason is to hide specific content from the public.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, you might want to <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/hide-wordpress-site-until-ready/\">hide your WordPress site until it’s ready</a> or want only to give your client access to preview your work.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Alternatively, you might have a <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-membership-website/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">membership website</a> and want to password protect content, so only subscribers have access.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whatever the reason, the result is a page where a password is required to gain access.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That said, when you lock a page or post in WordPress, the design is pretty basic.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll see a simple page with a box for entering a password and a submit button. The design usually reflects the <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/18-wordpress-premium-themes/\">WordPress theme</a> you’re using, but aside from that, there isn’t much you can do to make it more interesting.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Password-protected-page-preview.png\" alt=\"default WordPress password protected page without customizations\" class=\"wp-image-4747\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Password-protected-page-preview.png 650w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Password-protected-page-preview-400x245.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Yet if you customize protected pages, you can enhance your design with the following features:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Your brand’s logo to increase trustworthiness and keep your branding consistent</li><li>A custom message welcoming users and telling them how to access your protected content</li><li>Social media buttons to encourage users to follow your social channels</li><li><a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-a-contact-form-in-wordpress/\">Contact forms</a> for users to get in touch if they have any issues</li><li>Links to other areas of your website to promote your products and services.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Instead of having a basic page, you can turn locked pages into the perfect place to engage your visitors and generate leads.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Customize Password Protected Pages</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Customizing password-protected WordPress pages is a challenge if you’re not tech-savvy. Usually, you’d have to hire a developer to implement the design changes you need. That said, we understand that hiring expert help isn’t an option for many site owners.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that in mind, we&#8217;ll walk you through 4 methods to customize a password protected page in WordPress, with the help of 3 easy-to-use <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/best-wordpress-plugins/\">WordPress plugins</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Customize Password Protected Pages with SeedProd</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first method uses SeedProd, the <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/\">best Coming Soon Page plugin for WordPress</a> to customize password-protected posts and pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The powerful SeedProd builder and built-in design controls let you customize virtually every aspect of your page in minutes with <strong>no coding required</strong>. Even better, you can password protect your whole site or specific WordPress content with a few clicks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s look at the steps to customize protected pages in WordPress with SeedProd.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/pricing/\">get started with SeedProd here</a>, then follow these instructions for <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\">installing a WordPress plugin</a> to install and activate SeedProd on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Step 1: Password Protect Your WordPress Pages</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step is to protect your WordPress pages with a password. You can learn how to <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/password-protect-page-wordpress/#password-protect-an-entire-wordpress-site\">password protect pages in WordPress</a> using SeedProd here.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve done that, click the <strong>Edit Coming Soon / Maintenance Page</strong> button to open the SeedProd builder.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/edit-coming-soon-page-wordpress.png\" alt=\"edit your password protected page\" class=\"wp-image-4997\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/edit-coming-soon-page-wordpress.png 630w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/edit-coming-soon-page-wordpress-400x205.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Step 2: Choose a Page Theme</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>From the SeedProd builder page, click the <strong>Choose Theme</strong> button to select a theme for your page.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/choose-a-theme.png\" alt=\"Choose a theme to customize your WordPress password protect page\" class=\"wp-image-7011\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/choose-a-theme.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/choose-a-theme-400x302.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>SeedProd comes with several professionally designed themes to make setting up your password-protected page a breeze. Choose a theme that matches your desired look as closely as possible. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/seedprod-themes.png\" alt=\"SeedProd prebuilt page builder themes\" class=\"wp-image-7012\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/seedprod-themes.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/seedprod-themes-400x241.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then when you click it, it’ll be automatically added to your page builder.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Step 3: Customize Your Page Content</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, SeedProd enables several content features on your page including:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>A welcome message</li><li>Optin-form</li><li>Countdown timer</li><li>Social profile buttons</li><li>Contact form</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can disable or enable those features by choosing the appropriate section in the left-hand sidebar and sliding the toggle to the disabled position.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/disable-page-features.png\" alt=\"Enable and disable page features\" class=\"wp-image-7013\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/disable-page-features.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/disable-page-features-400x273.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s also easy to edit the content to include specific instructions for people viewing your page. Simply expand the section you need and change the content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, we want to include a password input field on our page, so users have to type a password for access.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To do that, expand the <strong>Content</strong> section and paste the shortcode <strong>seed_bypass_form</strong> into the content editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/add-password-input-field.png\" alt=\"Add the password input field onto your customized page\" class=\"wp-image-7014\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/add-password-input-field.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/add-password-input-field-400x205.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Step 4: Publish Your Customized Password Page</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’re happy with the customizations for your protected WordPress page, it’s time to publish it.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To publish a password protected page in WordPress using SeedProd, click the <strong>Save</strong> button, then click the <strong>Back to Settings</strong> link at the top of the builder.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/save-changes.png\" alt=\"Click save and then the back to settings link.\" class=\"wp-image-7015\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/save-changes.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/save-changes-400x221.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This takes you back to the General Settings page. From there, click <strong>Enable Coming Soon Mode</strong> and click the <strong>Save All Changes</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/publish-password-protect-WordPress-page.png\" alt=\"Publish your customized password protected page in WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-7016\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/publish-password-protect-WordPress-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/publish-password-protect-WordPress-page-400x230.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now when you navigate to your locked pages, you’ll see your customized design in place.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customized-password-protect-page.png\" alt=\"Customize WordPress password protect page\" class=\"wp-image-7017\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customized-password-protect-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customized-password-protect-page-400x271.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Customize Protected Form Pages with WPForms</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s also possible to customize password-protected form pages in WordPress. Then anyone trying to access specific forms on your site will have to enter a password.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to do that is to make a password protected form in WordPress using <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">WPForms</a> with the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-locker-addon/\" target=\"_blank\">Form Locker addon</a>. Then you can customize the page containing your form with the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-pages-addon/\" target=\"_blank\">Form Pages addon</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s look at the steps needed to customize protected forms next.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-password-protect-wordpress-forms-step-by-step/#with-addon\" target=\"_blank\">make a password-protected form</a> using these instructions. Then make sure you’ve activated the Form Pages addon.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can do that by navigating to <strong>WPForms » Addons</strong> and making sure the <strong>Form Pages</strong> addon status is set to <strong>Active</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/wpforms-form-pages-addon.png\" alt=\"Activate the WPForms form pages addon\" class=\"wp-image-7018\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/wpforms-form-pages-addon.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/wpforms-form-pages-addon-400x193.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, head to <strong>WPForms » All Forms</strong> and click <strong>Edit </strong>on the form you created in the previous step.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/edit-password-protect-form.png\" alt=\"Edit your WordPress password protect form\" class=\"wp-image-7019\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/edit-password-protect-form.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/edit-password-protect-form-400x194.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then click the <strong>Settings</strong> tab and choose the <strong>Form Pages</strong> option. On the right-hand side, check the <strong>Enable Form Pages Mode</strong> box, and further settings will appear.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/enable-form-pages.png\" alt=\"Enable the form pages mode\" class=\"wp-image-7020\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/enable-form-pages.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/enable-form-pages-400x155.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can enter a title and message for your form page and choose a custom permalink. Then you can add a custom logo image and choose a color scheme that matches your site’s branding.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customize-form-pages.png\" alt=\"Customize your password protected form page\" class=\"wp-image-7021\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customize-form-pages.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customize-form-pages-400x227.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember to click the <strong>Save</strong> button to preserve your changes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now when you navigate to that particular form’s page, you’ll see a modern, customized password-protected form with its own dedicated page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customized-password-form.png\" alt=\"Customized WordPress password protect form\" class=\"wp-image-7022\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customized-password-form.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customized-password-form-400x240.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Customize Protected Form Pages in SeedProd</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way to customize password-protected form pages in WordPress is to use a combination of SeedProd’s page builder and WPForms.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, create a password-protected form using the instructions linked earlier, then navigate to <strong>Settings » Coming Soon Pro</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the <strong>Advanced</strong> options panel, click the <strong>Include URLs option</strong>, and paste the page where your protected form is published. Now click the <strong>Save All Changes</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/password-protect-a-specific-page.png\" alt=\"Include your form page\'s URL\" class=\"wp-image-7023\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/password-protect-a-specific-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/password-protect-a-specific-page-400x260.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, scroll back to the top of the page and click the <strong>Edit Coming Soon / Maintenance Page </strong>button to open the SeedProd page builder.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now expand the <strong>Content</strong> section and click the <strong>Add Form</strong> button. This reveals a lightbox popup where you can choose a form from the dropdown menu.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/add-a-password-protected-form.png\" alt=\"Choose your form from the dropdown list\" class=\"wp-image-7024\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/add-a-password-protected-form.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/add-a-password-protected-form-400x295.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Select your password-protected form to embed it in your content area automatically.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/password-protected-form-in-customized-page.png\" alt=\"Your form automatically embeds in your page\" class=\"wp-image-7025\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/password-protected-form-in-customized-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/password-protected-form-in-customized-page-400x286.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>From now on, when users navigate to your form page, they’ll have to enter a password to unlock it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customized-password-protect-page-with-form.png\" alt=\"Customized WordPress password protect page with password protected form\" class=\"wp-image-7026\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customized-password-protect-page-with-form.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customized-password-protect-page-with-form-400x312.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. Customize Default Password Pages with CSS Hero</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Our final solution for customizing WordPress pages protected with passwords is to edit your CSS with a visual editor plugin. This means you can edit the CSS of any page without having to edit the code manually.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For this method, we’re using <a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/go/css-hero/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">CSS Hero</a>, one of the best plugins for easily customizing your WordPress site by pointing and clicking.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>CSS Hero is ideal for customizing the standard page you see when <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/password-protect-page-wordpress/#password-protect-a-page-in-wordpress\">password protecting WordPress</a> using the default WordPress visibility option.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So instead of a password page like the one below, you can pinpoint each area individually and change the look.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Password-protected-page-preview.png\" alt=\"Default WordPress password protected page\" class=\"wp-image-4747\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Password-protected-page-preview.png 650w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Password-protected-page-preview-400x245.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To do this yourself, <a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/go/css-hero/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">get CSS Hero here</a> and install the plugin on your website. Then navigate to your password-protected page in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now from the WordPress admin bar at the top of your page, click the <strong>Customize with CSS Hero</strong> option.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customize-with-css-hero.png\" alt=\"Customize your password protected page with CSS hero\" class=\"wp-image-7027\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customize-with-css-hero.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customize-with-css-hero-400x196.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will reveal a simple point-and-click visual editor you can use to customize your page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/css-hero-editor.png\" alt=\"Use the CSS Hero Editor to customize your WordPress password protect page\" class=\"wp-image-7028\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/css-hero-editor.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/css-hero-editor-400x287.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, to customize the background color for the header area, simply click it to open the options panel on the left-hand side. Then you can choose a color from the color picker tool.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customize-the-header.png\" alt=\"Customize the CSS of your header\" class=\"wp-image-7029\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customize-the-header.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customize-the-header-400x210.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To change your background color, click your page’s background and choose a color or gradient from the list. You can also add your background image.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/add-a-background-gradient.png\" alt=\"add a background gradient to your password protected page\" class=\"wp-image-7030\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/add-a-background-gradient.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/add-a-background-gradient-400x242.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The only drawback with using CSS Hero is that you can’t add crucial elements like contact forms, signup forms, social buttons, and so on. For that, we suggest using the SeedProd method above.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Continue customizing your page, clicking different elements, and adding custom colors and fonts.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then when you’re happy with your design, click the <strong>Save and Publish</strong> button and click the <strong>Quit</strong> icon in the top-right corner of your screen.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/save-page-design.png\" alt=\"click Save Changes then quit to exit the page designer\" class=\"wp-image-7031\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/save-page-design.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/save-page-design-400x286.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will take you to your newly edited password protected page, complete with its’ custom design.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customized-password-page.png\" alt=\"WordPress password protect page customized with CSS Hero\" class=\"wp-image-7032\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customized-password-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/customized-password-page-400x232.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There you have it!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Customizing Password Protected Pages is Easy</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>While customizing protected pages in WordPress can seem like a daunting task, it doesn’t have to be. Using the methods above, you can create stunning locked pages without having to write a single line of code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And with SeedProd’s handy page builder, you won’t have to start from scratch and can include essential lead generation elements like optin forms to <strong>grow your business</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So what are you waiting for?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/pricing/\">Get started with SeedProd today.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped you learn how to customize a password protected page in WordPress easily. For updates on more useful content like this, please go ahead follow us on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/seedprodwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/seedprod\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-password-protected-page-wordpress/\">How to Customize a Password Protected Page in WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"How To Customize the WordPress Login Page\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-the-wordpress-login-page/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-the-wordpress-login-page/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 08 Jul 2020 12:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"How To\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"customize WordPress login page\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"seedprod\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"wpforms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://seedprod.dev/?p=2293\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:398:\"<p>Want to customize your WordPress login page? Learn how to change the logo on the WordPress login page along with other customization using these plugins.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-the-wordpress-login-page/\">How To Customize the WordPress Login Page</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Stacey Corrin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22149:\"\n<p>Do you want to customize the WordPress login page for your website? If you run a membership site or an online store, your users will need a login page. So customizing the default WordPress login area will help you reflect your brand and offer a better user experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to customize the WordPress login page with 2 different methods.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a table of contents to help you navigate this article. Click any section you need to jump straight to it:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#why-create-a-custom-login-page\">Why create a custom login page?</a></li><li><a href=\"#choosing-the-right-login-page-plugin\">Choosing the right login page plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#method-1-using-login-page-pro\">Method 1: Using Login Page Pro</a></li><li><a href=\"#method-2-creating-a-login-page-with-wpforms\">Method 2: Creating a Login Page with WPForms</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Before we start, let&#8217;s explore why creating a custom login page in WordPress is a smart idea.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"why-create-a-custom-login-page\">Why Create a Custom Login Page in WordPress?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, the WordPress login page shows the WordPress branding and logo. If you&#8217;re a small blog or website, this is perfectly fine because you&#8217;re likely the only person with admin access.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/default-wordpress-login-page-800x594.jpg\" alt=\"The Default WordPress Login Page\" class=\"wp-image-2295\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/default-wordpress-login-page-800x594.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/default-wordpress-login-page-400x297.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/default-wordpress-login-page-768x570.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/default-wordpress-login-page.jpg 823w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But if your site lets people become registered users and login to your dashboard, a customized login page offers a better, more professional user-experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you use your own design and logo, users feel more at home because they recognize your branding. However, if you send users to a login screen that looks nothing like your website, it could look suspicious to inexperienced users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Furthermore, the default WordPress login screen doesn&#8217;t have anything but the login form. So you can&#8217;t take advantage of the space to promote other pages or craft a custom message for your users.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/customized-login-page.png\" alt=\"Customized WordPress login page\" class=\"wp-image-6958\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/customized-login-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/customized-login-page-400x249.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With this in mind, let&#8217;s explore the different methods to customize your login page in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"choosing-the-right-login-page-plugin\">Choosing a Plugin to Customize the WordPress Login Page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to create a custom WordPress login page is to use a <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/best-wordpress-plugins/\">WordPress plugin</a>. WordPress plugins extend the functionality of your website, helping add extra features without needing to hire a developer or mess around with code yourself.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ll walk you through creating a custom login page using the best WordPress plugins for the job, <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-custom-login-page/\">Login Page Pro</a>, by SeedProd and <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"method-1-using-login-page-pro\">Method 1: Using Login Page Pro</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Login Page Pro is a premium WordPress plugin offered on checkout when purchasing the SeedProd Coming Soon Page plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/login-page-pro.png\" alt=\"Login page pro WordPress plugin\" class=\"wp-image-6959\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/login-page-pro.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/login-page-pro-400x269.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There is a free version available on the WordPress repository called <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/custom-login-page-wp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Custom Login Page</a> that lets you make the most requested edits such as, changing the background, login text, page fonts, and colors of your login page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But if you want to add more functionality and branding to your page, it&#8217;s best to pay for the pro version.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to being able to perform all the edits you can in the free version, you can also perform the actions listed below on your login page.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Edit the Login Page Logo Alt Text and Logo Link</li><li>Add a message above or below the login page form</li><li>Change any of the text on the page page. For example, change the Username/Email or Password Label.</li><li>Add a color overlay to your background image</li><li>Add a background slideshow or video on the login page</li><li>Change the white login form background to any color or make it transparent.</li><li>Change the position of the login form</li><li>Change the color of any element on the WordPress login page</li><li>Integrated with Google Fonts</li><li>Add Social Media Profiles to the WordPress Login Page</li><li>Add a Google Recaptcha to the WordPress Login Page</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Click here to get started with <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-custom-login-page/\">Login Page Pro by SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then follow the steps below to customize your WordPress login page with this plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 1: Install and Activate Login Page Pro</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step is to download and install the Login Page Pro plugin on your WordPress website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re unfamiliar with how to do that, check out this <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">step-by-step guide to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After installing and activating the plugin, you&#8217;ll see the SeedProd welcome page where you can enter your license details and view the quick start video.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/enter-login-page-pro-license-key.png\" alt=\"Enter your Login Page Pro license key details\" class=\"wp-image-6960\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/enter-login-page-pro-license-key.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/enter-login-page-pro-license-key-400x228.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 2: Edit Your Login Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To start editing your login page, navigate to <strong>Settings » Login Page Pro</strong> from your WordPress dashboard. This takes you to the login page settings where you can enable, disable, and edit your login page. By default, the login page is set to <strong>Disabled</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/edit-login-page.png\" alt=\"Edit your login page \" class=\"wp-image-6961\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/edit-login-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/edit-login-page-400x242.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click the <strong>Edit Login Page</strong> button to start customizing your page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The next screen you see will be the default WordPress login page on the right-hand side, while on the left are the options to customize your page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/login-page-builder-screen.png\" alt=\"the login page pro builder screen\" class=\"wp-image-6962\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/login-page-builder-screen.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/login-page-builder-screen-400x203.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s start by customizing the login page logo.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 3: Customize The Login Page Logo</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To add a new logo to your login page, click the logo heading on the left, then click the <strong>Choose Image</strong> button. This lets you choose a logo from your WordPress media library, or upload one from your computer.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/add-new-logo.png\" alt=\"Add a new logo to your login page\" class=\"wp-image-6963\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/add-new-logo.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/add-new-logo-400x200.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After, you can add a URL and some Alt text for your logo. This helps users navigate back to your main website.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/logo-alt-text.png\" alt=\"Adjust your logo alt text and margins\" class=\"wp-image-6964\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/logo-alt-text.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/logo-alt-text-400x288.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also adjust the margin at the bottom of your logo to reduce space.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 4: Customize The Login Form Text</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The next step is to customize the text on your login form by clicking the <strong>Customize Text</strong> heading.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/customize-login-form-text.png\" alt=\"Customize your login form text\" class=\"wp-image-6965\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/customize-login-form-text.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/customize-login-form-text-400x318.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In this area, you can enter a message before and after your form, change the form text, error messages, and button label.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 5: Add a Custom Background Image</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now let&#8217;s look at adding a custom image to your login page background. To do that, click the <strong>Background Settings</strong> heading.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/login-page-background-color.png\" alt=\"Choose your login page background color\" class=\"wp-image-6966\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/login-page-background-color.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/login-page-background-color-400x273.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can use the color palette to choose a color for your background, or click the <strong>Choose Image</strong> button to upload a photo.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/upload-background-image-1.png\" alt=\"Upload a background image for your login page\" class=\"wp-image-6967\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/upload-background-image-1.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/upload-background-image-1-400x314.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Below that, you can add an overlay color to the background to make your page elements stand out and choose how you&#8217;d like the image to display. For example, it can cover the whole page, or auto fit the page container.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/background-overlay-options.png\" alt=\"Add an overlay for your login page background\" class=\"wp-image-6968\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/background-overlay-options.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/background-overlay-options-400x312.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Alternatively, you can create a slideshow background by uploading multiple images or enter the URL of a video to use a video background.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/custom-background-slideshow.png\" alt=\"Add a slideshow or video background to your custom login page\" class=\"wp-image-6969\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/custom-background-slideshow.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/custom-background-slideshow-400x312.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember to click <strong>Save</strong> periodically to preserve your settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 6: Customize Your Buttons, Colors, and Fonts</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The next few headings deal with your login page&#8217;s styling.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Form Container</strong> heading gives you the ability to adjust the margins and padding in your page&#8217;s form. You can also change the position of the form, its opacity, and add an animation.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Button Style</strong> section lets you change the color of your login button, and give it a flat style.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/button-styles.png\" alt=\"Customize the WordPress login page with different button styles\" class=\"wp-image-6970\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/button-styles.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/button-styles-400x278.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After that, you can change the color of your form&#8217;s text, background, and error messages.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/form-colors.png\" alt=\"Customize the color of your form\'s login page\" class=\"wp-image-6971\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/form-colors.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/form-colors-400x247.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Below Form Links</strong> section lets you hide the forgot password and back link on your login page. You can also give those links a custom color to stand out if needed.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/below-form-links.png\" alt=\"Customize the link that appear below your login page form.\" class=\"wp-image-6972\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/below-form-links.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/below-form-links-400x255.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then there&#8217;s the <strong>Typography</strong> section. This is where you can choose from a vast range of Google Fonts to match your site&#8217;s branding and theme. Then you can change the font weight, size, and height to get things looking just right.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/login-form-typography.png\" alt=\"change the fonts on your custom login page\" class=\"wp-image-6973\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/login-form-typography.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/login-form-typography-400x262.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 7: Add Your Social Profile Buttons</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another stand-out feature of Login Page Pro is the ability to add custom social icon buttons to your WordPress login page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply click the <strong>Social Profile</strong>s heading and click the <strong>Add Profile Link</strong> button to add a social channel.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/social-profile-links.png\" alt=\"Enter your social profile links and icons to display on your custom login page\" class=\"wp-image-6974\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/social-profile-links.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/social-profile-links-400x270.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There are 19 different social icons to choose from when you click the drop-down arrow beside the URL field. Then in the link field, add the URL for your social media profile.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below that, you can adjust your social profile buttons&#8217; size and choose to open them in a new tab when clicked.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After this section, is an area to enter <strong>Custom CSS</strong> to customize your login page further. Then you can use the <strong>Advanced</strong> section to enable ReCaptcha for your page, and import, or export your settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/custom-css.png\" alt=\"Enter your custom CSS\" class=\"wp-image-6975\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/custom-css.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/custom-css-400x289.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you&#8217;re happy with how everything looks, click <strong>Save</strong>, and the <strong>Back to Settings</strong> link.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/save-settings.png\" alt=\"Save your custom login page settings\" class=\"wp-image-6976\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/save-settings.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/save-settings-400x314.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 8: Enable your Custom WordPress Login Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you&#8217;ve finished customizing your login page, it&#8217;s time to make it live for your website users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To do that, click <strong>Enable Custom Login Page</strong> from the General Settings page and click <strong>Save All Changes</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/enable-login-page.png\" alt=\"Enable your custom login page in WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-6977\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/enable-login-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/enable-login-page-400x184.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now when users visit your login page, they&#8217;ll see the custom design you just created.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/customized-WordPress-login-page.png\" alt=\"Customized WordPress login page\" class=\"wp-image-6978\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/customized-WordPress-login-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/customized-WordPress-login-page-400x316.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"method-2-creating-a-login-page-with-wpforms\">Method 2: Using WPForms to Create a Custom Login Page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The second method to customize the WordPress Login Page we&#8217;ll cover today involves using the popular WPForms plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/wpforms.jpg\" alt=\"Wpforms best form builder plugin\" class=\"wp-image-5990\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/wpforms.jpg 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/wpforms-400x232.jpg 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>WPForms is the best drag and drop form builder for WordPress. And what you might not realize is that you can use it&#8217;s handy <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/user-registration-addon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">User Registration addon</a> to build a login page for your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With over <strong>3 million</strong> website owners using WPForms to build smarter forms and surveys, you can be confident knowing you&#8217;re in good hands.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So if you don&#8217;t need a plugin dedicated to creating login pages, follow this step-by-step tutorial for <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-custom-login-form-for-improved-site-branding/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to create a WordPress custom login form</a> using WPForms.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped you learn how to customize the WordPress login page for your website. Now you can keep your site looking professional and offer an excellent user experience for your customers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So what are you waiting for?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click here to <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/pricing/\">get started with Login Page Pro</a> today.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And don&#8217;t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/seedprodwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/seedprod\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a> for more helpful tips and tutorials.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-the-wordpress-login-page/\">How To Customize the WordPress Login Page</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-the-wordpress-login-page/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"How to Create a Giveaway Landing Page that Converts\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-a-giveaway-landing-page/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 24 Jun 2020 12:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"How To\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"giveaway landing page\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"rafflepress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"wordpress plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=6884\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:390:\"<p>Want to create a landing page for your website? We\'ll show you easy ways to create a giveaway landing page that converts for maximum leads.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-a-giveaway-landing-page/\">How to Create a Giveaway Landing Page that Converts</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Stacey Corrin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41443:\"\n<p>Running a giveaway is an easy way to attract your ideal audience to your brand&#8217;s website. But converting those visitors into verified entries and potential customers isn&#8217;t as straightforward.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Without a giveaway landing page, visitors get distracted easily. That can result in fewer people entering your giveaway and less qualified leads for your business. That&#8217;s why building a landing page for your giveaway is crucial for ensuring your contest&#8217;s success.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But don&#8217;t worry if you don&#8217;t know how to create one. This article will show you how to create a giveaway landing page that converts your target audience into leads and sales for your brand.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a table of contents to help you navigate this post:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-table-of-contents uagb-toc__align-left uagb-toc__columns-undefined uagb-block-a9a2989f\" data-scroll=\"true\" data-offset=\"30\" data-delay=\"800\"><div class=\"uagb-toc__wrap\"><div class=\"uagb-toc__title-wrap\"><div class=\"uagb-toc__title\">Table Of Contents</div></div><div class=\"uagb-toc__list-wrap\"><ul class=\"uagb-toc__list\"><li><a href=\"#why-you-need-a-giveaway-landing-page\">Why You Need A Giveaway Landing Page</a></li><li><a href=\"#elements-of-a-giveaway-landing-page\">Elements of a Giveaway Landing Page</a></li><li><a href=\"#10-excellent-giveaway-landing-page-examples\">10 Excellent Giveaway Landing Page Examples</a></li><li><a href=\"#how-to-create-a-giveaway-landing-page\">How to Create a Giveaway Landing Page</a></li><li><a href=\"#advertise-your-giveaway-landing-page\">Advertise Your Giveaway Landing Page</a></li><li><a href=\"#test-your-landing-page\">Test Your Landing Page</a></li></ul></div></div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"why-create-landing-page\">Why You Need A Giveaway Landing Page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A giveaway landing page isn&#8217;t merely a place to add your giveaway details. <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-a-simple-landing-page/\">Creating a landing page</a> for your contest lets you hone in on your giveaway, making it the main focus for website visitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sure you could post your contest on any old post or page. But chances are those pages have other information on them like:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Advertising banners</li><li>Coupons and special offers</li><li>Links to popular blog posts</li><li>Call to action buttons for products</li><li>Social media feeds</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s an example of a giveaway page with too much going on.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/distracting-giveaway-page.png\" alt=\"Distracting giveaway page\" class=\"wp-image-6885\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/distracting-giveaway-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/distracting-giveaway-page-400x221.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With so many elements on your page, visitors could overlook your giveaway altogether.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yet a dedicated giveaway landing page is free of those distractions and puts the focus on your contest.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-landing-page.png\" alt=\"distraction free giveaway landing page\" class=\"wp-image-6818\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-landing-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-landing-page-400x320.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That way, you can show people exactly what you want them to do and what steps to take to make it happen.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"elements-of-giveaway-landing-page\">Elements of a Giveaway Landing Page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Before we get into the &#8220;how-tos&#8221; of creating a giveaway landing page, let&#8217;s look at the critical elements every landing page should have. It&#8217;ll be easier to put yours together and get the results you want by understanding what makes a high-converting landing page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Attention-Grabbing Copy</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The copy on your landing page should jump off the page and tell your visitors how awesome it is that they&#8217;re there. People should get excited by reading your copy and imagine winning your prize.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-landing-page-copy.png\" alt=\"Create compelling giveaway landing page copy\" class=\"wp-image-6886\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-landing-page-copy.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-landing-page-copy-400x306.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you set the scene with your words, visitors will want to sign up to enter immediately.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Eye-Catching Images</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You also need a visual element that engages your landing page visitors right away. That could be an image of the grand prize, a background image, or even a video welcoming people.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-landing-page-images.png\" alt=\"Create eye-catching images for your giveaway landing page\" class=\"wp-image-6887\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-landing-page-images.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-landing-page-images-400x333.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The visual content on your page sets the tone for the type of contest you&#8217;re running.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Sharing Options</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Making your giveaway landing page easy to share is vital if you want to spread the word. While some people will copy and share your landing page&#8217;s URL, most won&#8217;t. So you need to make it as simple as possible to do so.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-sharing-options.png\" alt=\"Add easy options to share your giveaway landing page\" class=\"wp-image-6888\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-sharing-options.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-sharing-options-400x228.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>One way to do that is to ask people to share your giveaway in return for more entries. You can also send an email confirming people&#8217;s entries, a thank you for entering, and a request to share your giveaway with their friends.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. Easy Ways to Enter</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If it&#8217;s difficult to enter your giveaway, visitors will lose interest and abandon the page. Instead of adding complex <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-a-wordpress-user-registration-form-with-custom-fields/\">sign up forms</a>, you can use a contest app that lets people enter with a couple of clicks. This removes the frustration from lengthy forms and offers instant satisfaction when they enter.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/easy-entry-methods.png\" alt=\"Offer easy ways to enter on your giveaway landing page\" class=\"wp-image-6889\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/easy-entry-methods.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/easy-entry-methods-400x318.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Even better, if it&#8217;s easy to enter your giveaway, it gives people more incentive to share it. It&#8217;s all about creating a fun and seamless experience for users.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>10 Excellent Giveaway Landing Page Examples</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s not always easy coming up with ideas from scratch. But don&#8217;t worry. Below we&#8217;ve put together a list of excellent <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/giveaway-landing-page-examples/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\"undefined (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">giveaway landing page examples</a> you can use as inspiration for your next contest.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Glendalough Gin Giveaway Landing Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/gin-giveaway-landing-page-1.png\" alt=\"Glendalough Gin giveaway landing page\" class=\"wp-image-7133\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/gin-giveaway-landing-page-1.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/gin-giveaway-landing-page-1-400x315.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For this giveaway, the restaurant wanted to promote its Glendalough Gin evening with a contest.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using the RafflePress giveaway builder, they quickly created a giveaway landing page with clear instructions on what users would win and how to enter.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By including an image of the prize, it&#8217;s easy to imagine being a winner. Plus, their restaurants&#8217; background image makes it easier for participants to recognize the restaurant in person.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The stand out element of this contest is RafflePress&#8217;s viral refer-a-friend action, with instructions for participants to refer other people for bonus entries.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/refer-a-friend-actions-min.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7063\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/refer-a-friend-actions-min.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/refer-a-friend-actions-min-400x335.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Oak Ridge Free Trash Collection Giveaway Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/trash-collection-contest-landing-page.png\" alt=\"Oak Ridge giveaway contest landing page\" class=\"wp-image-7134\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/trash-collection-contest-landing-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/trash-collection-contest-landing-page-400x297.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A similar contest that uses the RafflePress giveaway landing page feature is this giveaway from Oak Ridge trash collectors. They used the widgets&#8217; prize details area to show their logo over an image representing the business to convey what&#8217;s up for grabs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They also highlighted the prize in all caps, which makes it stand out from the rest of the page, so there&#8217;s no doubt what users could win. The background image of their vehicle ties everything together into a well-branded contest.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Underground Dining Valentines Meal Giveaway</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/valentines-contest-landing-page.png\" alt=\"Valentines Day giveaway landing page\" class=\"wp-image-7135\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/valentines-contest-landing-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/valentines-contest-landing-page-400x289.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Underground Dining used the perfect time of the year to promote their business by running a Valentine&#8217;s giveaway for a meal for two.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By building the contest with RafflePress&#8217;s giveaway builder, they created an engaging landing page, setting the tone for a romantic treat. And with their copy, they included all the details of the prize with redemption requirements.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Again the company used the Refer a Friend action to increase the reach of their contest, securing bonus entries for participants.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. Clubbing TV Headphones Giveaway Landing Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/brand-partnership-giveaway-landing-page.png\" alt=\"Brand partnership giveaway landing page example\" class=\"wp-image-7136\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/brand-partnership-giveaway-landing-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/brand-partnership-giveaway-landing-page-400x258.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For this contest, Clubbing TV partnered with edeejay.com to offer their community a chance to win a Mackie Studio &amp; DJ headphone pair.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Partnerships like this are a great way to engage the audiences of both brands to increase leads and sales.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using the RafflePress contest landing page builder, they gave participants a distraction-free opportunity to win a relevant prize. They also used images related to their industry, which are ideal for creating an emotional response to spur users into entering.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>5. CLEAN Cause Backyard BBQ Giveaway</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/bbq-giveaway-landing-page-1.png\" alt=\"BBQ Giveaway landing page example\" class=\"wp-image-7138\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/bbq-giveaway-landing-page-1.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/bbq-giveaway-landing-page-1-400x220.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In this giveaway, CLEAN Cause gave users the chance to win a bundle of BBQ goodies that included their own products. This is an excellent way to offer a high-value prize that attracts tons of entries while promoting their business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On visiting the landing page, it&#8217;s clear to see what the contest is about from the high-quality photo and prize list. Plus, it&#8217;s instantly easy to see how you can enter.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you were to create this contest with RafflePress, you could use the Join an Email Newsletter action, so entering takes less time.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/join-email-list-action.png\" alt=\"Join an email newsletter giveaway action rafflepress\" class=\"wp-image-7139\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/join-email-list-action.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/join-email-list-action-400x319.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Since RafflePress integrates with popular <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/best-email-newsletter-services/\">email marketing services</a>, you can connect to your favorite with a few clicks. Then all users will need is to enter their email address to take part.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>6. RunPhones Headphones Contest</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/runphones-contest-landing-page.png\" alt=\"RunPhones contest landing page example\" class=\"wp-image-7140\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/runphones-contest-landing-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/runphones-contest-landing-page-400x280.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>RunPhones created a similar contest offering users the chance to win 2 wireless headphones. The landing page does an excellent job of promoting their products and helps users imagine what it would be like to use the prize.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Instead of displaying a separate <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-a-wordpress-user-registration-form-with-custom-fields/\">registration form</a> on their landing page, they could have used the Join an Email Newsletter action to keep all entries in one place.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s an example we whipped up in a few minutes using RafflePress that offers a much more user-friendly experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/runphones-rafflepress-giveaway-landing-page.png\" alt=\"RunPhones contest landing page example using RafflePress\" class=\"wp-image-7141\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/runphones-rafflepress-giveaway-landing-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/runphones-rafflepress-giveaway-landing-page-400x286.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>7. Golfballs.com Sweepstakes Landing Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/golfballs-sweepstakes-landing-page.png\" alt=\"golfballs.com sweepstakes landing page example\" class=\"wp-image-7142\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/golfballs-sweepstakes-landing-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/golfballs-sweepstakes-landing-page-400x208.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For this giveaway landing page example, Golfballs.com ran sweepstakes to promote their business with the prize of a set of personalized golf balls.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They&#8217;ve done a great job making their page eye-catching, with clear examples of what users can win. And with a simple sign-up form, they&#8217;re able to gather email addresses to <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/5-benefits-of-building-an-email-list-and-how-to-start-today/\">grow their list quickly</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To go a step further, they could have used RafflePress to <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/how-to-run-a-photo-contest/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\"undefined (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">run a photo contest</a> where participants could design their own personalized golf balls. Then they could enter using the Upload an Image action with a few clicks.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/rafflepress-submit-an-image-action.png\" alt=\"RafflePress submit an image action\" class=\"wp-image-7143\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/rafflepress-submit-an-image-action.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/rafflepress-submit-an-image-action-400x279.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This type of contest would give the company user-generated content (UGC) to promote their products in the future. Plus, UGC is much more effective in persuading people to buy a product than simple brand messaging because it comes from genuine users.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>8. Ashley HomeStores Mattress Sweepstakes</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/sweepstakes-landing-page-example.png\" alt=\"Sweepstakes landing page example\" class=\"wp-image-7144\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/sweepstakes-landing-page-example.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/sweepstakes-landing-page-example-400x214.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another smart contest landing page is this example from Ashley HomeStores. They ran weekly sweepstakes to promote Tempur-pedic mattresses, which is an excellent way to promote their company.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The imagery on this page does a fantastic job of creating an emotional response in the reader. Yet to enter the sweepstakes, users have to click a button, which adds unnecessary steps.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The more steps participants have to follow, the less likely they are to complete the actions to enter your giveaway. So it&#8217;s best to keep your entry requirements as simple as possible.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To combat this, they could have used the built-in landing page with RafflePress&#8217;s giveaway widget. Then as soon as people visited the page, they could enter right away.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>9. Dell&#8217;s Storage Virtual Road Trip Prize Draw Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/dell-storage-giveaway-landing-page-example.png\" alt=\"Dell storage virtual road trip giveaway landing page example\" class=\"wp-image-7145\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/dell-storage-giveaway-landing-page-example.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/dell-storage-giveaway-landing-page-example-400x231.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Dell&#8217;s landing page is a fantastic example of creativity in action. They created a virtual road trip through scenic storage landscapes to educate users about their storage products.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After taking part, users have to answer a question for the chance to win a prize with a new contest and question every week.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s pretty easy to create a similar contest for your business. Instead, you could ask users to watch a video first or read a blog post. Then you can use the Answer a Question action in RafflePress for users to enter your giveaway.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/answer-a-question-entry-action.png\" alt=\"RafflePress answer a question entry action\" class=\"wp-image-7146\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/answer-a-question-entry-action.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/answer-a-question-entry-action-400x272.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When the next week comes around, you can easily click to duplicate the previous weeks&#8217; contest, edit the title and question, and publish it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/duplicate-giveaway-rafflepress.png\" alt=\"How to duplicate a giveaway in RafflePress\" class=\"wp-image-7147\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/duplicate-giveaway-rafflepress.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/duplicate-giveaway-rafflepress-400x264.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>10. Rush Charge Portable Battery Bank Giveaway</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/amazon-gift-card-giveaway-landing-page.png\" alt=\"Rush Charge Max giveaway landing page example\" class=\"wp-image-7148\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/amazon-gift-card-giveaway-landing-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/amazon-gift-card-giveaway-landing-page-400x394.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Rush Charge&#8217;s example of a giveaway landing page demonstrates how you can make any contest to match your website&#8217;s branding.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Even better is the level of detail about the giveaway prize. This leaves no doubt about what you could win while offering valuable information about how to use it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If we were to recreate this contest with RafflePress, we&#8217;d display all the information in the giveaway widget with their high-quality prize image. And Instead of adding a separate sign-up form, we&#8217;d use the Join a Newsletter action to add users to our email list.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then when it comes to choosing a giveaway winner, it&#8217;s easy to view all entries in the giveaway dashboard and <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/how-to-pick-a-winner-of-a-giveaway/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\"undefined (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">pick a winner</a> randomly.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/choose-a-giveaway-winner.png\" alt=\"choose a giveaway winner\" class=\"wp-image-7073\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/choose-a-giveaway-winner.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/choose-a-giveaway-winner-400x189.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>No doubt you&#8217;re eager to try these examples yourself now. But how do you create a landing page for your next contest? Let&#8217;s find out next!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"how-to-create-landing-page\">How to Create a Giveaway Landing Page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Most giveaway landing pages start as a blank page. Then you have to design the look and feel of the page, add all your contest details, and <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-multi-step-form-wordpress/\">create forms</a> for people to enter.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating a giveaway landing page from scratch takes a lot of work. And if you don&#8217;t have much experience building web pages, it&#8217;ll be hard to get things looking how you want.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to create a giveaway landing page is to use giveaway software like RafflePress.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">RafflePress, the best WordPress giveaway plugin</a>, makes it easy to grow your email list, traffic, and followers with contests. With its ready-made giveaway templates, you&#8217;ll never have to build contests from scratch again.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The giveaway builder offers easy ways to design your contest using pre-made templates. Plus, verified entry methods give visitors the ability to enter with a single click while eliminating fraud entries.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/contest-entry-actions.png\" alt=\"contest entry actions\" class=\"wp-image-6813\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/contest-entry-actions.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/contest-entry-actions-400x267.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Even better, RafflePress has a distraction-free <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/giveaway-landing-page-examples/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">giveaway landing page</a> optimized to get you the best results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For this tutorial, we&#8217;ll use RafflePress to show you how to create your contest&#8217;s landing page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Get started with RafflePress here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Create Your Contest With RafflePress</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve downloaded the RafflePress plugin, you need to create a plan, so you know what you want to get out of running a giveaway.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your plan should include the following information:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Who your target audience is</li><li>What your contest goals are</li><li>The type of contest you&#8217;ll run</li><li>Your giveaway rules and eligibility</li><li>A time-frame for running your contest</li><li>How you&#8217;ll promote your giveaway</li><li>Your method for drawing a winner</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ve put together a step-by-step guide to <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-an-online-contest/\">create an online contest</a> here, that includes all those details. It&#8217;ll also teach you how to create your first online contest with RafflePress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Design Your Giveaway Landing Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you&#8217;ve followed the steps to create a giveaway with RafflePress let&#8217;s look at designing your landing page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>RafflePress includes several ways to get your contest looking exactly how you want, including:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>The option to add images of your prize</li><li>Title and description areas to write your landing page copy</li><li>Several font styles to make your copy stand out</li><li>Different layouts for your giveaway widget</li><li>Custom colors for buttons</li><li>Custom <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/best-wordpress-landing-page-plugins/\">landing page</a> background colors</li><li>The ability to upload a custom background image</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s look closer at each option.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Adding Your Landing Page Copy</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>In the RafflePress giveaway builder, click the <strong>Details</strong> tab to see an overview of your contest widget. When you click the pencil icon under the <strong>Giveaway Prize Details</strong> section, you can edit your contest&#8217;s title.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/edit-contest-copy.png\" alt=\"add your landing page copy\" class=\"wp-image-6890\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/edit-contest-copy.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/edit-contest-copy-400x250.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the right-hand side of your screen, you can also add a description. Try to paint a picture of what winning your prize will look like, to encourage people to enter.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Upload a Prize Image</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>To add an image of your giveaway prize, click the <strong>Select Image button</strong>. Then you can upload an image or photo from your computer to display in the giveaway widget.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/select-contest-image.png\" alt=\"Choose an image for your giveaway landing page\" class=\"wp-image-6891\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/select-contest-image.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/select-contest-image-400x272.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you&#8217;re happy with how it looks, click <strong>Done Editing</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/save-giveaway-settings.png\" alt=\"Save your giveaway settings\" class=\"wp-image-6892\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/save-giveaway-settings.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/save-giveaway-settings-400x248.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember to save your giveaway often by clicking the <strong>Save</strong> button in the top-right corner.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Change the Contest Widget Layout and Font</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, click the <strong>Design</strong> tab to customize the layout, font, and colors of your giveaway.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Under the <strong>Layout</strong> heading, you&#8217;ll see 2 different ways to display your contest widget.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, you can display the header, text, and then your image.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-layout-1.png\" alt=\"Giveaway layout header, text, then image\" class=\"wp-image-6893\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-layout-1.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-layout-1-400x244.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Or you can show the image first, then the header and description text.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-layout-2.png\" alt=\"Giveaway layout with image, header, then text\" class=\"wp-image-6894\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-layout-2.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-layout-2-400x270.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Under the <strong>Fonts</strong> heading, you can choose from a drop-down list of different font pairings. This will help your giveaway stand out on your landing page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-fonts.png\" alt=\"Change your giveaway landing page fonts\" class=\"wp-image-6895\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-fonts.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-fonts-400x279.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Choose any fonts you like the best to see the changes in the preview on the right.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Add Custom Button Colors</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Changing the color of the main action button on your giveaway landing page is just as easy.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/contest-button-colors.png\" alt=\"Change your giveaway call to action button colors\" class=\"wp-image-6896\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/contest-button-colors.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/contest-button-colors-400x275.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply click the circle icon under the <strong>Button Color </strong>heading and choose a color from the palette. You can also enter more colors by adding your preferred hex value.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Changing Your Landing Page Background</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>The next section is the page background. This only applies to the background of your giveaway landing page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can choose a custom color for your background, or upload a background image.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/upload-background-image.png\" alt=\"Upload a background image for your giveaway landing page\" class=\"wp-image-6897\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/upload-background-image.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/upload-background-image-400x261.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To add a new background image, click the <strong>Select Image</strong> button and upload an image from your computer.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/preview-background-image.png\" alt=\"Preview of your background image\" class=\"wp-image-6898\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/preview-background-image.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/preview-background-image-400x247.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re feeling technical, you can enter your own <strong>Custom CSS</strong> to make your contest page stand out even more.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Publish Your Giveaway Landing Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When you&#8217;ve finished designing your landing page, it&#8217;s time to make it live.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To publish your giveaway on a landing page, click the <strong>Publish</strong> button at the top of the contest builder.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll see 3 different options for publishing your competition. But to publish it as a landing page, you&#8217;ll need to click the <strong>Giveaway Landing Page</strong> option.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Upon clicking that option, you can to set up your page&#8217;s permalink by clicking &#8220;click here&#8221; as shown below.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/set-landing-page-permalink.png\" alt=\"Click here to set up your landing page permalink\" class=\"wp-image-6899\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/set-landing-page-permalink.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/set-landing-page-permalink-400x204.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;re then taken to a screen where you can enter the URL for your page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-landing-page-permalink.png\" alt=\"Giveaway landing page permalink settigns\" class=\"wp-image-6900\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-landing-page-permalink.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-landing-page-permalink-400x167.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve entered the URL, click the <strong>View</strong> button to preview your page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/published-giveaway-landing-page.png\" alt=\"Published giveaway landing page\" class=\"wp-image-6901\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/published-giveaway-landing-page.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/published-giveaway-landing-page-400x317.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Congratulations! Now anyone visiting that specific page can enter for a chance to win.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"advertising-contest-landing-page\">Advertise Your Giveaway Landing Page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Since your landing page exists outside your normal navigation menu, visitors won&#8217;t be able to find it easily. That&#8217;s why after creating a giveaway landing page; you should promote it to ensure you get as many entries as possible.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-exit-intent-popup.png\" alt=\"Giveaway exit-intent popup\" class=\"wp-image-6902\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-exit-intent-popup.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/giveaway-exit-intent-popup-400x241.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There are several ways to promote your competition which we&#8217;ll explain below:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Add an <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/40-exit-popup-hacks-that-will-grow-your-subscribers-and-revenue/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">exit-intent popup</a> to catch people before they leave your website and direct them to your giveaway page.</li><li>Add a call-to-action in your website&#8217;s sidebar to notify people you&#8217;re running a giveaway they can enter.</li><li>Submit your landing page to <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/28-best-online-sweepstakes-websites-to-promote-your-contest/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">contest directory websites</a> to attract targeted traffic.</li><li>Share your giveaway on social media to raise awareness and generate excitement.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also check out these <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/contest-prize-ideas/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">proven contest promotion ideas</a> for more inspiration.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"test-giveaway-page\">Test Your Landing Page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There&#8217;s one more thing you should do to ensure the success of your giveaway, and that&#8217;s to test it. By testing your landing page, and analyzing your traffic, you can understand how well it&#8217;s working for your audience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One way to test your landing page is to use<a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"> MonsterInsights, the best WordPress analytics plugin</a>. With MonsterInsights, you can track visits to your contest&#8217;s landing page during your giveaway. And you can also see how visitors find your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/monsterinsights-dashboard-get-more-subscribers-800x556.jpg\" alt=\"monsterinsights wordpress dashboard\" class=\"wp-image-5924\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/monsterinsights-dashboard-get-more-subscribers-800x556.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/monsterinsights-dashboard-get-more-subscribers-400x278.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/monsterinsights-dashboard-get-more-subscribers-768x534.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/monsterinsights-dashboard-get-more-subscribers.jpg 1116w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>MonsterInsight&#8217;s dashboard reports, also let you see your data within your WordPress dashboard. That removes the need for you to leave your site and track your data elsewhere.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Even better, real-time statistics makes it easy to track your landing page traffic while your giveaway is running. Then you can make adjustments as you go to get the best results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know how to create a giveaway landing page that converts go ahead and get started!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you create a distraction-free landing page for your <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-make-giveaways-on-instagram/\">Instagram giveaway</a>, blog giveaway, and more, you tell visitors exactly what you want them to do. For participants, it&#8217;s a chance to win a fantastic prize, and for you, it&#8217;s more targeted leads to grow your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Get started with RafflePress today</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And don&#8217;t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/seedprodwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/seedprod\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a> for more helpful tips and tutorials</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-a-giveaway-landing-page/\">How to Create a Giveaway Landing Page that Converts</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Why You MUST Avoid SeedProd Nulled [7 Reasons]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"https://www.seedprod.com/seedprod-pro-nulled/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 17 Jun 2020 12:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"seedprod\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"seedprod coming soon pro nulled\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"seedprod nulled\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=6848\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:376:\"<p>If you\'re considering getting a nulled SeedProd Pro plugin, think again! In this article we explain why you MUST avoid SeedProd nulled at all costs.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/seedprod-pro-nulled/\">Why You MUST Avoid SeedProd Nulled [7 Reasons]</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Stacey Corrin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17460:\"\n<p>At times we&#8217;re asked if it&#8217;s OK to download a free version of SeedProd Pro and use a nulled SeedProd license key. But the truth is, nulled plugins are unofficial copies of paid WordPress products. And you should avoid them if you care about the security of your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So in this article, we&#8217;ll show you why you must avoid SeedProd nulled, particularly if you&#8217;re serious about protecting your online business and reputation.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What Is a Nulled Plugin?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A nulled plugin is a copy of a premium WordPress plugin people unethically distribute on the internet.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some people argue it&#8217;s OK to copy and distribute nulled plugins because WordPress and its derivative works are licensed under the General Public License (GPL).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A GPL gives you the right to…</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Run the software however you like</li><li>See how the software works</li><li>Redistribute the software</li><li>Improve the software</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>So while it&#8217;s true WordPress is licensed under GPL, using unofficial copies can negatively impact your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not only does it cause honest, small WordPress companies to lose money, it also impacts the security of websites using nulled plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why You Should Avoid SeedProd Coming Soon Pro Nulled</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/avoid-seedprod-nulled.png\" alt=\"Why you should avoid SeedProd Pro nulled\" class=\"wp-image-6849\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/avoid-seedprod-nulled.png 630w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/avoid-seedprod-nulled-400x190.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Most small businesses look for ways to keep their costs low when building websites. It&#8217;s in our nature to find ways to save money, after all.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you research the implications of using nulled WordPress plugins, it&#8217;s clear why cutting costs with a nulled SeedProd license key isn&#8217;t such a good idea.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are several crucial reasons why you must avoid using SeedProd nulled on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Security Risks</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>SeedProd Coming Soon Pro nulled versions are dangerous for your website. They can negatively impact your <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-security/\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress security</a> because plugin cracks often carry malware.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That malicious code can spread through your website files and database, making it difficult to find and remove. And that&#8217;s even if you knew where to look, which many website owners don&#8217;t.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If search engines like Google detect malware distributed on your site, you&#8217;re in for some bad news. Because it&#8217;s likely those search engines will either send your rankings plummeting or de-index your site altogether.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/spam-links-nulled-plugin.png\" alt=\"Security risks with nulled SeedProd plugins\" class=\"wp-image-6850\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/spam-links-nulled-plugin.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/spam-links-nulled-plugin-400x234.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine all the hard work you put into building your rankings and site traffic, disappearing overnight.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All because of a hack implemented through the nulled SeedProd plugin you chose to install.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Scary stuff!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Privacy Issues</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/security-issues.png\" alt=\"Privacy issues with SeedProd coming soon Pro nulled\" class=\"wp-image-6851\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/security-issues.png 630w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/security-issues-400x190.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But it&#8217;s not just your website nulled software can hurt either. Downloads of SeedProd Pro nulled software can contain several types of hidden, harmful code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And amongst that malware could be code designed to steal information from your site and give it to hackers and criminals hiding out on the dark web.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Having that information stolen can expose sensitive personal information such as email addresses and passwords. If you run an <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ecommerce-optimization-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">eCommerce website</a> or membership site, your customers&#8217; personal information could be at risk.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>No doubt, you&#8217;ve heard the fallout from companies with customer data breaches in the news. It isn&#8217;t pretty, and can significantly damage your business reputation, which isn&#8217;t easy to salvage.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>More importantly, hacks are hard to detect and can go unnoticed for a long time. Your website might appear to work normally when, in reality, the hackers are behind the scenes with plenty of time to do their damage.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Harmful to SEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As we touched upon earlier, if you get a SeedProd license key for free and download a pirated plugin, you could obliterate your search engine rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Nulled SeedProd Coming Soon Pro plugins are known to add spam links to your website. Spam links are low-quality links that are out of context with the rest of your site&#8217;s content. Many nulled plugins include code that injects spam links on your site to build backlinks to equally spammy websites quickly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Even more worrying is that those links can hijack your visitors, redirecting them to potentially dangerous websites designed to extract sensitive information.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The problem is, the malicious code triggering those events is hard to spot. They hide deep inside your site&#8217;s code, making them hard to detect for the untrained eye.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Chances are you won&#8217;t even be able to figure out which links are redirecting your visitors because if you&#8217;re a site administrator, they won&#8217;t redirect you personally.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But search engines do notice spam links, and they notice them fast. That&#8217;s when they&#8217;ll penalize your site for having so many spammy links, pushing your site back down search rankings, or completely de-indexing your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/nulled-theme-start-website-again.png\" alt=\"Nulled SeedProd plugins are harmful to your SEO\" class=\"wp-image-6852\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/nulled-theme-start-website-again.png 620w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/nulled-theme-start-website-again-400x303.png 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;ll take months to recover from getting penalized by search engines, and even longer to build your SEO back up again. It could get to the point where the easiest option is to start your site all over again from scratch.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Do you really want to go through all that?</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. No Access to Plugin Support</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Even the most experienced site owners need support from time to time. Whether it&#8217;s from documentation for setting up SeedProd&#8217;s features or one-on-one help from our customer support team, the help is there when you need it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The SeedProd team is a close-knit crew 